<subsection xml:id="subsec-complementary-and-supplementary-angles">
    <title>Complementary and Supplementary Angles</title>
    <p>
        A <term>complementary angle</term> is one of two angles whose sum is exactly 90°. This means that when two angles are complementary, they form a right angle together.
    </p>
    <p>
        Angles that add together to make a straight line are called <term>supplementary angles</term>. 
        If you know one supplementary angle you can subtract it from <m>180^\circ</m> to find a missing angle.
    </p>

